From 4d122ce9c65308d73eaf0ba3a78cd172e661c23c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bitsy <bitsydoge@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 22:46:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Add OpenType variable font axis API

Add TTF_GetNumFontAxes(), TTF_GetFontAxisInfo(), TTF_SetFontAxisValue()
and TTF_GetFontAxisValue() so applications can enumerate a variable
font's 'fvar' axes and adjust their design coordinates (wght, wdth,
opsz, GRAD, FILL, ...) at runtime.

These wrap FreeType's FT_Get_MM_Var / FT_Get_Var_Design_Coordinates /
FT_Set_Var_Design_Coordinates. The FT_MM_Var metadata is queried lazily
and cached on the font, then freed with FT_Done_MM_Var in TTF_CloseFont.

Setting an axis reuses the same invalidation path as TTF_SetFontSizeDPI:
recompute metrics, Flush_Cache() (which bumps the font generation so
text engines rebuild), UpdateFontText(), and hb_ft_font_changed() under
HarfBuzz. Tags use the existing TTF_StringToTag()/TTF_TagToString()
convention. Fonts with no variation axes report zero axes and behave
exactly as before.

Add examples/variablefont.c demonstrating axis enumeration and setting
the 'wght' axis, and regenerate the export lists.
---
 CMakeLists.txt             |   1 +
 examples/variablefont.c    | 109 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 include/SDL3_ttf/SDL_ttf.h | 108 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/SDL_ttf.c              | 181 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/SDL_ttf.exports        |   4 +
 src/SDL_ttf.sym            |   4 +
 6 files changed, 407 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 examples/variablefont.c

